[{"id":"VH979863","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of two students sitting on a horizontal seesaw with a fulcrum at its center. The student sitting on the left side of the seesaw is indicated as Student X and the student sitting on the right is indicated as Student Y with mass m sub Y.\" height=\"161\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979863.g06.png\" width=\"330\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two students, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, sit on a seesaw that is in static equilibrium, as shown in the figure. A fulcrum is located at the center of the seesaw. The mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub Y\"><math alttext=\"m sub Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is known. A third student, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Z\"><math alttext=\"Z\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Z</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, must determine the mass of Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following measurements should Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Z\"><math alttext=\"Z\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Z</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> make in order to determine the mass of Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>? Justify your selection.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979863_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The length of the seesaw, because the entire length of the seesaw is in static equilibrium.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The distance that Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is from the edge of the seesaw and the distance that Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is from the edge of the seesaw, because the seesaw would no longer be in static equilibrium if one or both students moved closer to the edge of the seesaw.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The distance that Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is from the center of the seesaw and the distance that Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is from the center of the seesaw, because these are the distances from the fulcrum to the location of the forces exerted on the two-student-seesaw system.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mass of the seesaw, because a force due to gravity is exerted on the seesaw from Earth.</p>"],"answer":2}]